{{Background|file=Joy Amidst the Clouds.jpg}}{{Headerbox|file=Joy Amidst the Clouds.jpg|header=Eternal joy... As long as you remain.}}{{Class 1|hexagon=🎡|color-h=-150|color-s=70%|color-l=50%|header=Survival Difficulty: Class|class=1d - Dreamful|safety=Safe|security=Stable, Secure, and Mental Supportive|entity=Dream-Related Hazards}}

'''Level 387''', otherwise referred to as "Joy Amidst the Clouds" or "Sky Ferris Wheels," is the 388th level of [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]]. It was discovered on August 27th, 2000, by [[M.E.G.]] explorers.

== Description ==
{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Joy Amidst the Clouds.jpg|caption=The most known image of '''Level 387'''.}}
'''Level 387''' possesses the appearance of a vast skyscape, packed with a collection of colossal, eternal clouds that endlessly float around '''Level 387''' without ever disappearing. In the entirety of '''Level 387''', one can notice a number of carnival and amusement park attractions spread around the level, atop some stronger clouds, the stronger clouds can support thousands of times their weight and compose a third of all clouds in this level. '''Level 387''' possesses a rudimentary day-night cycle, and the skyline is dotted by many stars, planets, nebulae, and galaxies, each with their own features and properties that make them quite easy to differ.

These clouds on '''Level 387''' behave differently from the ones on [[Level 386]] and [[Level 385]]. They are described as fluffy and partially solid, being solid enough for one to stand on; they are often summarized and compared to pillows of cotton. These clouds support more weight than the ordinary [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]] cloud; they maximally support the weight of 20 humans and small machinery; however, the cloud will tear apart, like a blanket, if something exceedingly heavy is placed on it, such as, for instance, a large-scale vehicle or machine. These clouds float around the level and may enter areas like a pillow thrown through a window. Due to their properties, they can be used for transport and sleeping.

The winds on '''Level 387''' are fairly quick, and clouds travel fast around the level. The temperatures in the region are sufficiently cold, striking roughly 8-27° Celsius (46,4-80,6° Fahrenheit). The humidity of the air at '''Level 387''' is above average, as a result, some fog and even more clouds being spread around the level. The clouds on '''Level 387''' carry non-toxic chemicals responsible for their whimsical coloring and hue. These chemicals may spread around the air and skyscape and modify the horizon and sky's coloring and tinting. However, these chemicals, when situated somewhere in high quantities, may cause some strange mental issues and excessive behavior; these can be identified by random rainbow spots placed about the clouds. A wanderer should be careful when around these spots and use a respirator.

{{Blurimage|file=Clouds Amidst the Joy.jpg|align=right|caption=The cloudscape.}}

'''Level 387''' contains dream-related hazards, which are very similar to those of [[Level 386]]; per the Manifestation Event, any figures that appear on a wanderer's dreams will manifest within '''Level 387''' as a hallucination, scent, sound, taste, or touch. These hallucinations have been reported by wanderers many times on the level and some even reported that the hallucinations feel as real as any wanderer; having scent, producing sounds, moving about as realistically as a human, etc. However, the Manifestation Event, differently from that on [[Level 386]], wanderers have reported these hallucinations to be able to manifest pain, sadness, pleasure, pressure, nausea, and many other senses.

As aforementioned, around '''Level 387''', there are structures and buildings broadly scattered, specifically amusement park attractions and toys. The amusement park attractions range from ferris wheels (the most common), merry-go rounds, carrousels, rollercoasters, etc. These contain anomalous properties; for example, they are nearly unbreakable and built solely from metal and plastic, advanced tools are required to take one of these apart. Using any of the attractions is considered mental supportive and will increase the wanderer's joy, and cause similar effects to [[Object 1|Almond Water]]. There are hidden wooden bridges that connect most of the clouds on '''Level 387''', making the transportation and movement around the level much easier for wanderers. These bridges are tight, and their collapse would be very unlikely.

The ferris wheels are the main feature of '''Level 387'''; they are the most common structures and are encountered every 100 meters. They are built of metal, and each pod on them is a color of the rainbow, and their center is an 8-pointed, white star. Each pod on the ferris wheels causes a certain amount of joy depending on the wanderer's preferences; for example, a pink pod may not cause as much joy as a yellow one. The ferris wheels spin at a desired, shared speed by the majority of wanderers at the attraction.

{{Blurimage|file=As a sky.jpg|caption=One of the many rooms on the Outer Side.|align=right}}
The joy expressed and reported by wanderers is beyond anything ever described on [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]]. A joy that cannot be ceased quickly and that lasts days before fading. There is no possible method to stop the joy. The joy is described as being near one of the happiest moments possible in a human life. While it is unknown what causes this such high amount of joy, it is believed that the whimsical scenario and nostalgia invoked are one of the contributing factors to this.  

There is an object named "Cloud Water" on '''Level 387''', which is composed of water, vanilla, and a small concentration of the clouds. Cloud Water contains mental supportive properties that make drinkers much happier, replicating the effects of the ferris wheels and the clouds. Cloud Water is categorized as Object 387. Cloud Water can be encountered quite uncommonly on reserves, bottles, puddles, etc., being the most common resource on the level.  

=== The Outer Side ===
The Outer Side is an unstable region situated a few kilometers from the main areas of '''Level 387''' and is often considered the border of the level. It is quite similar to the remaining level; however, the area appears to be devoid of gravity, causing all structures to float around the Outer Side. Some structures of the Outer Side are not found anywhere else in '''Level 387'''; for example, there are a number of floating, unfurnitured rooms hidden across the Outer Side, along with many other similar structures. Like on its sister levels, the Outer Side serves as a passage from '''Level 387''' to [[Level 386]] and [[Level 385]].  

Some of the structures on the Outer Side include small buildings, skyscrapers, stores, planks, cabins, apartments, malls, bridges, and many other structures that strangely come across as being adapted to existing on an almost entirely gravity-devoid sky, other than containing a modifying and slightly odd layout. These buildings are empty, dim-lit, unfurnitured, and yet seem to be frequently maintained and taken care of, several resources are hidden behind walls and taped on the ceilings. These buildings may be engulfed by the clouds of '''Level 387''' that fill the room with the chemicals, which may cause several hazards. Once clouds enter a room, only the wind will be able to take them out of there, and the clouds can attract wind to said room.   

{{Blurimage|align=right|file=As a sky 2.jpg|caption=A room being engulfed by clouds.}}

Similarly to other areas, the Outer Side is slightly unstable, resulting in no-clipping being prominent on the Outer Side, adjacent to other strange gravitational properties and moments of instability. Despite that, the Outer Side is fully habitable, and many small groups have built outposts around the Outer Side. Transportation is quite easy on the Outer Side, as the low gravity and the areas with no gravity are generally easy to traverse, and one does not need to be concerned regarding falling down.  

A notable feature on the Outer Side is the Sky Metro, which is a metro system that passes through many areas of '''Level 387'''. The Sky Metro manifests itself as an ordinary European metro; it is very clean and hygienic, modern, and technological. There are several vending machines within the Sky Metro that sell [[Achrophiline]], Cloud Water, and [[Object 1|Almond Water]], etc., sold not only on the machines but on mini-freezers, closets, shelves, and counters that are placed on "store" areas of the train. There are miniatures of the attractions spread around the Sky Metro, and especially the ferris wheels and merry-go-rounds. Playing with the miniatures will entertain the wanderer and modify their perception of time, depending on how much fun they are having.    

== Entities ==
The only entities one can find on '''Level 387''' are [[Tornadoes]]. Although it is quite difficult to encounter them.

== Human Settlements ==
There are hundreds of small colonies of 3-50 people, but only one major outpost on '''Level 387'''.

=== The Joy-Makers ===
The Joy-Makers are a small group of 150 people who inhabit '''Level 387''' to use the attractions and assist wanderers on their stay within '''Level 387'''. They create advertisements and send them to other levels; they also create manuals for each attraction and accept very easily any volunteering, possible new employees. The employees are paid with resources, which they can visit during breaks. The employees of the Joy-Makers generally describe their job as fun and with a high salary.

== Entrances and Exits ==

=== Entrances: ===

* Some paintings on [[Level 385]] may resemble '''Level 387''', no-clipping through them will take one here.
* There are parts of [[Level 386]], [[Level 385]], and '''Level 387''' which overlap each other, long stays may take one to one of these levels.
* Being engulfed by clouds on [[Level 993.1]].
* '''Level 387''' is theorized to be accessible from [[Level 993]].
* Upon climbing a pylon resting under a cluster of clouds in [[Level 392]].
*
*
*

=== Exits: ===

* Falling off the level will take one to [[Level 97]], [[Level 392]] or [[the Void]].
* Entering a building will take one to [[Level 97]].
* The pink seat on ferris wheels will cause one to no-clip into [[Level 399]].
* Drinking Cloud Water may take one to [[Level 413]].
* The Outer Side overlaps with [[Level 385]] and [[Level 386]], therefore, one could enter them by no-clipping.
* Entering a door with a wooden frame may lead to [[Level 27]].
*
